==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Megalocyte
<hw>Meg"a*lo*cyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Megalo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a hollow vessel.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A large, flattened red blood cell corpuscle
having no nucleus, twice the diameter of the ordinary red corpuscle,
found in considerable numbers in the blood in profound
anaemia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Megalomania</ent>⟦br⟧
